  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nThere is line 20 in `src/app/global/local_app_settings.nim`\r\n\r\n```let DEFAULT_FAKE_LOADING_SCREEN_ENABLED = defined(production) and not TEST_MODE_ENABLED #enabled in production, disabled in development and e2e tests```\r\n\r\ni clarified with @alexjba  and he said if I have env variable set as `export STATUS_RUNTIME_TEST_MODE=true` that should eventually consider this TEST_MODE_ENABLED as enabled and as a result, i should be able to see some certain toggle (Fake loading screen) in the app as **switched off**.\r\n\r\nit is not happening. So even I have this env variable set, i am seeing the toggle in the app as ON all the time. The only way to see it off - is to use local build (dev build).\r\n\r\nI need this to be working as this will help me to reduce the time of the automation tests for 30s per each app launch which is a lot",
